Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The elements in the input array `arr` are integers.

Postconditions:
- The returned value is an integer representing the minimum number of steps to reach the last index of the array.
- The returned value is non-negative.
- If the length of the input array `arr` is 1, the returned value is 0.
- If the length of the input array `arr` is greater than 1, the returned value is the minimum number of steps required to reach the last index of the array.